channel.title: When I log in the screen is black! 77 errors?
channel.description:
Well, I was just on my server and then I tried to put in a code and now I can't log in. Any help?
[IMG]http://i999.photobucket.com/albums/af115/smdplawks/fail.jpg[/img]
[IMG]http://i999.photobucket.com/albums/af115/smdplawks/assss.jpg[/img]
Also, does anyone know a code that 2x your player count? I need it because my server is new and I want to encourage people to stay.

item.title: When I log in the screen is black! 77 errors?
item.dc:creator: @Plewz Plewz
item.description:
@Plewz wrote:

It should say in your playercount void like, count++ or something like that.

Just do:

count++ * 2

item.title: When I log in the screen is black! 77 errors?
item.dc:creator: @Plewz Plewz
item.description:
@Plewz wrote:

Seems your error is from a string in the server called: King,

Search king in your source to see if you forgot something after it such as a ; or it’s not spaced right.

For 2xing player count, goto your playerhandler.java and simply add * 2 to your getplayercount void.
